sql:
SELECT generation_id
FROM performance_data
WHERE mean_score > 0.8;

SELECT DISTINCT generation_id 
FROM performance_data 
ORDER BY generation_id;

SELECT generation_id 
FROM performance_data 
ORDER BY generation_id ASC;

SELECT generation_id, mean_score
FROM performance_data
ORDER BY mean_score DESC;

SELECT generation_id
FROM performance_data
WHERE mean_score = (SELECT MAX(mean_score) FROM performance_data);

external_knowledge:
- A generation refers to a simulation run with a unique identifier (generation_id); 
- The latest report for a generation is the one with the most recent creation timestamp; 
- The last access for a generation refers to the most recent access log with a descending creation timestamp.
